-> Strings are defined as a stream of characters. Strings are used to represent text and are generally represented by enclosing text within quotes 
-> There is an extra terminating character which is the Null character ('\0') used to indicate the termination of string which differs strings from normal character arrays.

Function Of String
   Function           Defination                                                                                              ` Declaration
1) getline()        	This function is used to store a stream of characters as entered by the user in the object memory.        getline(cin, str);
